# Fizz Claude theme deploy

Live store theme **Fizz Claude** (`#188495003933`, store `g9rykd-jt.myshopify.com`) must be deployed from **`fizz-claude-theme/`** only.

## Do

```bash
shopify theme push --path fizz-claude-theme --store g9rykd-jt.myshopify.com --theme "Fizz Claude" --allow-live
shopify theme pull --path fizz-claude-theme --store g9rykd-jt.myshopify.com --theme "Fizz Claude"
```

- Edit Claude design in `fizz-claude-theme/` (sections like `fizz-hero`, `fizz-statement`).
- Before push, confirm homepage is Claude: `index.json` uses `fizz-hero`, **not** `fizz-ss-hero`.

## Do not

```bash
# BAD — overwrites Fizz Claude with Kinetic Spark (SS) homepage
shopify theme push --path fizz --store g9rykd-jt.myshopify.com --theme "Fizz Claude" --allow-live
```

- Do not push `--path fizz` to theme **"Fizz Claude"** or theme id `188495003933`.
- Do not treat `fizz-test-61526` as the live Claude theme.

## Why

| Folder | Default `index.json` | Role |
|--------|----------------------|------|
| `fizz-claude-theme/` | Claude (`fizz-hero`, …) | Live **Fizz Claude** theme |
| `fizz/` | Kinetic Spark (`fizz-ss-*`) | Combined theme; Claude only via `*.fizz-claude.json` suffixes |

If Claude edits also exist under `fizz/sections/fizz-claude-*`, keep `fizz-claude-theme/` in sync, but **only** push `fizz-claude-theme/` to the live Fizz Claude theme.
